## Phase 1: Extract Core as FFI Library

### Duration: 2-3 days

### New Structure

```
core/
├── src/
│   ├── lib.rs              # exports all modules
│   ├── engine.rs           # GStreamer (no changes)
│   ├── controller.rs
│   ├── model.rs
│   ├── config.rs
│   ├── media_library.rs
│   ├── shuffle.rs
│   ├── duration_cache.rs
│   └── ffi.rs              # NEW: C FFI bindings
├── include/
│   └── sparkamp.h          # NEW: C header for Swift
└── build.rs                # builds as .dylib
```

### Steps

1. Create `core/` as a separate Cargo workspace member in `Cargo.toml`
2. Move from `src/` → `core/src/`:
   - `engine.rs` — GStreamer (no changes needed)
   - `controller.rs` — playback state machine
   - `model.rs` — Track, Playlist, shuffle logic
   - `config.rs` — TOML config
   - `media_library.rs` — SQLite
   - `shuffle.rs` — shuffle history
   - `duration_cache.rs` — duration persistence
   - `duration_probe.rs` — background duration probing
   - `skin.rs` — CSS loading (cross-platform)
3. Skip plugin-related files (deferred):
   - `plugin_abi.rs`
   - `plugin_manager.rs`
   - `loaded_plugin.rs`
   - `plugin_settings.rs`
   - `viz_plugin.rs`
   - `filetype_plugin.rs`
4. Write `include/sparkamp.h` C header
5. Write `core/src/ffi.rs` implementing the FFI
6. Build as `.dylib` (macOS dynamic library)
7. Write `core/build.rs` to handle GStreamer linking

### C Header Design

```c
// include/sparkamp.h

#ifndef SPARKAMP_H
#define SPARKAMP_H

#include <stdint.h>
#include <stdbool.h>

#ifdef __cplusplus
extern "C" {
#endif

// ── Lifecycle ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

void spark_init(void);
void spark_shutdown(void);

// ── Player Controls ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

int  spark_load(const char* uri);
int  spark_play(void);
int  spark_pause(void);
int  spark_stop(void);
void spark_seek(double seconds);
void spark_set_volume(double vol);              // 0.0–1.0
void spark_set_eq_band(int band, double db);   // band 0-9, db -24 to +12
void spark_set_preamp(double mult);             // 0.5–1.5
void spark_set_eq_enabled(bool enabled);

// ── Queries ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

double spark_position(void);    // seconds
double spark_duration(void);    // seconds
int    spark_state(void);      // 0=stopped, 1=playing, 2=paused
int    spark_poll_bus(void);   // 0=none, 1=EOS, 2=error, 3=duration-changed

// ── Playlist ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

void spark_pl_clear(void);
void spark_pl_add(const char* path);
void spark_pl_remove(int index);
void spark_pl_reorder(int from, int to);
int  spark_pl_len(void);
int  spark_pl_current(void);
void spark_pl_set_current(int index);

// ── Track Info (caller must free returned strings) ────────────────────────

char* spark_track_title(int index);
char* spark_track_artist(int index);
char* spark_track_album(int index);
char* spark_track_path(int index);
double spark_track_duration(int index);
void   spark_free_string(char* s);

// ── Config ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

void spark_config_load(void);
int  spark_config_save(void);

// ── Callbacks (Swift registers these) ────────────────────────────────────

typedef void (*SparkPositionCallback)(double position, double duration, void* ctx);
typedef void (*SparkEOCallback)(void* ctx);
typedef void (*SparkErrorCallback)(const char* error, void* ctx);
typedef void (*SparkDurationCallback)(double duration, void* ctx);

void spark_set_position_callback(SparkPositionCallback cb, void* ctx);
void spark_set_eocallback(SparkEOCallback cb, void* ctx);
void spark_set_error_callback(SparkErrorCallback cb, void* ctx);
void spark_set_duration_callback(SparkDurationCallback cb, void* ctx);

#ifdef __cplusplus
}
#endif

#endif // SPARKAMP_H
```

### FFI Implementation Pattern

Follow existing patterns from `src/plugin_abi.rs`:

```rust
// core/src/ffi.rs

use std::os::raw::{c_char, c_double, c_int, void as c_void};
use std::ffi::{CStr, CString};

// Re-export all core types
pub use crate::engine::Player;
pub use crate::controller::Controller;
pub use crate::model::Playlist;
pub use crate::config::Config;

static mut PLAYER: Option<Player> = None;
static mut PLAYLIST: Option<Playlist> = None;
static mut CONFIG: Option<Config> = None;

static mut POSITION_CALLBACK: Option<unsafe extern "C" fn(c_double, c_double, *mut c_void)> = None;
static mut POSITION_CALLBACK_CTX: *mut c_void = std::ptr::null_mut();

#[no_mangle]
pub unsafe extern "C" fn spark_init() {
    // Initialize GStreamer, load config, playlist
    gstreamer::init().ok();
    // ... rest of init
}

#[no_mangle]
pub unsafe extern "C" fn spark_load(uri: *const c_char) -> c_int {
    let uri_str = CStr::from_ptr(uri).to_string_lossy();
    PLAYER.as_mut().unwrap().load(&uri_str)
}
```

